Spain May Extend Unemployment Payment, El Economista Reports

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-07-21T07:06:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/spain-may-extend-unemployment-payment-el-economista-reports.html
Spain ’s Labor Minister Valeriano Gomez may extend a 400-euro ($571) monthly payment to unemployed
people,  El Economista  reported, citing the minister.  The labor ministry may also implement a training program to
take almost 600,000 young people off unemployment, the newspaper
said, citing Labor Secretary of State Mari Luz Rodriguez.  A labor ministry spokeswoman wasn’t able to confirm the
report to Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
